  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6756.7 sitting right in the thick negative gamma zone between 6745-6765 (-6.6B at 6765), dealers are positioned to amplify moves and are likely buying this dip aggressively as part of their short gamma hedging. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (+5.4B) should act as strong resistance if we rally, with dealers selling into strength there. The gex_surge event combined with the -47.5% 1-min GEX change suggests we're seeing rapid position adjustments, but the overall PIN regime means dealers will work to contain volatility and push price back toward the 6723 flip level.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect dealers to support the market here but cap rallies near 6800.",
